SYNTAX — Command and Selector Syntax

SECTOR SPECIFICATIONS
  Most commands accept a sector spec as an argument.

  *                     all sectors you own
  0,0                   single sector at relative (0,0)
  -3:3,-3:3             rectangle: x from -3 to 3, y from -3 to 3
  0,0:5                 all sectors within 5 of (0,0)
  #1                    realm 1 (defined with 'realm' command)

SECTOR CONDITIONALS  (?des=X)
  Append ?des=X directly to any spec (no space) to filter by
  sector designation letter.  For commands like threshold, deliver,
  and distribute, the condition must be part of the same argument:

    *?des=h               all your harbor sectors
    #1?des=m              iron mines inside realm 1
    0,0:5?des=a           agribusiness within 5 of capital
    *?des=f               all food factories

  Designation letters:
    c  capital      h  harbor       f  food factory    a  agribusiness
    m  iron mine    e  tech school  l  library         r  research lab
    +  oil well     !  oil refinery  i  shell industry  w  warehouse
    u  uranium mine g  gold mine    d  dust factory     b  bank
    s  shell dump   k  lcm factory  j  hcm factory      (see 'info sectors')

SHIP SPECIFICATIONS
  *                     all your ships
  0                     ship uid 0
  0-5                   ships 0 through 5

COMMODITY LETTERS
  c=civ  m=mil  u=uw   f=food  s=shell  g=gun  p=petrol
  i=iron d=dust b=bar  o=oil   l=lcm    h=hcm  r=rad

HEX DIRECTIONS
  u=upper-right  j=right   n=lower-right
  b=lower-left   g=left    y=upper-left
  h=stop         v=view (look without moving)

EXAMPLES
  census *?des=a            census of all agribusiness sectors
  threshold food *?des=a 30 set food threshold in all agri sectors
  threshold iron #1?des=m 100  keep 100 iron in realm 1 iron mines
  deliver f #2?des=a 200 $  all agri in realm 2 deliver food to dist
  distribute #1 4,6         point all realm 1 sectors to warehouse

